description: Ms. Fragments of a Latin book of hours written in the Netherlands about l500, with mainly German additions written in Cologne in the 17th cent. The additions include Latin liturgical texts with music (leaves 145a-150a). Former owners: a community (or member of a community) of women at or near the church of Sankt Maria im Capitol in Cologne; Geheim-Justizrat Barnheim; Rev. Edwin A. Dalrymple. Library of Congress.
